Also starred in track and basketball (was recruited by top programs, including Syracuse, Georgia Tech and Cincinnati). As a true freshman in 2008, teamed with Lions '09 No. 1 overall selection Matthew Stafford to produce 56-963-8 (17.2) in 13 games (11 starts at flanker). Dealt with a strained groin in preseason camp and in December. Started 8-of-10 games in which he played at flanker in '09, leading Bulldogs receivers with 53-808-6 (15.3). Also blocked a field-goal attempt. Suffered a pulmonary contusion against Florida and sat out against Tennessee State, then sprained his left AC joint against Auburn and missed two more games. Did not start against LSU or Tennessee (formation). Was suspended for the first four games of the '10 season after selling game jersey to a suspected agent. Started 8-of-9 games played at flanker (non-start was due to formation) and tallied 57-848-9 (14.9) receiving with two punt returns for 25 yards (12.5).
